---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="How FidoHikes tests products, researches content, and maintains editorial independence.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-800 text-earth mb-6">Editorial Policy</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        At FidoHikes, we take our recommendations seriously. Your dog's safety and comfort depend
        on the gear and advice we share, so we hold ourselves to high standards.
      </p>
      <h2>How We Test Products</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We purchase most products ourselves — no pay-for-play reviews</li>
        <li>Products are tested on real trails and camping trips, not just unboxed on a desk</li>
        <li>We evaluate durability, comfort, safety, and value over multiple uses</li>
        <li>We update reviews when products change or when we have new long-term findings</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>How We Research Content</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Trail and destination information is verified against official park/land management sources</li>
        <li>Health and safety advice references veterinary guidelines and published research</li>
        <li>We note when regulations or trail access may have changed since publication</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Our content is never influenced by affiliate partnerships, sponsorships, or brand relationships.
        We disclose all material connections and maintain full editorial control over what we publish.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
